parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to be difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when turning left.
symptoms: The vehicle is hard to turn
especially to the left
the steering wheel feels stiff or heavy
the vehicle jerks or pulls to the right when turning left
loss of power steering assist.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rack and pinion can cause the vehicle to be difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when turning left.
symptoms: The vehicle is hard to turn
especially to the left
the steering wheel feels stiff or heavy
the vehicle jerks or pulls to the right when turning left
grinding or clunking noises when turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine compartment fires can cause damage to the vehicle, surrounding property, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke or flames coming from the engine compartment
burning oil or coolant odors
engine stalling or loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks and gasket failures can cause engine damage, stalling, and potentially lead to engine compartment fires.
symptoms: Oil leaks
burning oil or coolant odors
engine stalling or loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical and computer malfunctions can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power
warning lights or error messages on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracked intake manifolds can cause engine damage, stalling, and potentially lead to engine compartment fires.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power
burning oil or coolant odors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to loss of power steering and brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls when using the turn signals
headlights
or other electrical components; the dashboard lights and gauges malfunction; the vehicle catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to loss of power steering and brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls when using the turn signals; the ignition switch overheats; the vehicle is difficult to start or will not start at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signals can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to loss of power steering and brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The turn signals cause the vehicle to stall; the dashboard lights and gauges malfunction; the vehicle is difficult to control when the turn signals are used.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window regulators can cause the windows to fall out of their tracks, which can obstruct the driver's view and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windows fall out of their tracks; the windows malfunction; the electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to loss of power steering and brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine fails; the vehicle stalls; the vehicle catches fire.
